Project Statement – Simple Expense Tracker (Python):
The Simple Expense Tracker is a small and easy-to-use Python program made to help users keep track of their daily expenses and income. It works in the console and saves all data in a JSON file so the information stays safe even after closing the program.

Purpose:
The main purpose of this project is to give users—especially students—a simple way to understand where their money goes. Instead of using complicated apps, this tool offers a quick and clear method to record spending and view monthly totals.

Problem:
Most people forget their day-to-day expenses and end up overspending. Many available tools are confusing or require internet access. This project provides a simple, offline solution for basic financial tracking.

Objectives:
Let users add daily expenses and income.
Store all financial records neatly using JSON.
Show all past entries in one place.
Provide monthly summaries with total income, expenses, and balance.
Encourage better money management habits.

Scope:
The project focuses on essential features only, keeping it beginner-friendly. It can later be expanded with charts, budgets, login features, or a GUI.

Technologies Used:
Python 
JSON
Console-based user interface

Conclusion:
This Expense Tracker shows how Python can be used to solve real-life problems in a simple way. It helps users stay aware of their spending while also helping beginners practice Python file handling and basic logic.
